      "content": "i've tried all that. the walks, the talking, the \"one day at a time\" thing. it's just exhausting. it feels like i'm just performing being alive. like i'm just a ghost going through the motions. honestly, sometimes i think the only way to actually stop this feeling is to just... stop everything. to not have to wake up to the emptiness anymore. does that ever actually get better or is it just an endless cycle of pain?",
